text: [Music] Last time on Trebuchet Village, the gang accepted the quest of the mudmen to go slay the beast. Patrick Yodar used his survival skills from cosplaying as a poor person to track the beast, and on their way, they ran into a hunter, Goofus Tiedrich, who attempted to kidnap Prince Jumanji. But Dogen's magical dirt pouch and Patrick Yodar's keen eyes led to the boy's rescue. The gang then set upon Goofus, beating him so badly that they forced information out of him, learning about something called the Brave Lions, a notorious band of scaredy cats, elves, humans, dwarves, and the like, who have banded together to take down the terrifier kingdom, claiming that the normalization efforts by King Nardwuar are too little too late. Goofus was hired as a bounty hunter to kill the young Nardboy, or capture him, and so that our heroes would spare his life, he led them to the White Woman of the Woods as well, who lives in the pond further south. Upon meeting the white woman, Dogen jammed a javelin inside of Goof as far enough that it killed him. The white woman of the woods is a goodly spirit who wishes to banish the jester and his terrible reign over the whippet woods, especially the kitsunes who worship him and enslave her precious kugler elves. The jester made all of the creatures and plants weird and angry, like something out of Nightmare Before Christians. When the whip it was, it used to be normal, used to not make people laugh uncontrollably or have fucked up plants that try to kill you. The White Woman of Wood says that the Yoni Egg of Baskin, an ancient and powerful artifact, was stolen from her during the Great War long ago between the Terrifier and the police, which led to the Jester's rise in power. Now it is possessed by the vile warlock Connoria, who serves the jester in the woods, cursing its creatures with weirdness and laughter.
